rms.dao

Interface JdbcTemplateInterface<E>

  • Type Parameters:
    E - The data type of the java class and database schema you want to map between.
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BookingsJdbcTemplate, FeatureTypeJdbcTemplate, LocationJdbcTemplate, ResourcesJdbcTemplate, ResourceTypeJdbcTemplate, UsersJdbcTemplate, UserTypeJdbcTemplate, VisitorsJdbcTemplate

    public interface JdbcTemplateInterface<E>
    The jdbc template class supports methods to map between Java objects and database rows. Includes methods to insert, delete, update, search, and get all.
    Author:
    syntel

        Will delete a database row.
        Parameters:

      • update

        int update(E objectToUpdate)
        Will update an existing row in the database.
        Parameters:
        objectToUpdate - The java object containing all the new values to be updated. Will update the row with the same ID as the java object.
        Returns:
        The number of rows updated (Either 0 or 1)

      • search

        E search(int objectID)
        Will search for a database row and map it into a java object.
        Parameters:
        objectID - The ID of the row you want to search for.
        Returns:
